text: Who competes in the Olympics? Serious athletes. Those participating in sports of skill and equipment must break their own country's record while qualifying and not making the Olympics just to demonstrate their country's progress for supporting professional participation. Milk on a plane as though non-flyers don't deserve quality milk.  "The important thing in the Olympic Games is not the winning but the taking part."  "The important thing in life is not the triumph but the struggle." - Pierre de Coubertin 1896  The quote at the end is intended to cause the reader to believe they are observing the dieties of the afterlife in athletic competition. It causes one to compare the quality of life with the participants. Who is living?  My life in Ski jumping by Warren Sharp meant that he believed in this observance of Olympian athletic competition and considered all else beneath.  "There's life with each touch even when misunderstanding mocks."
